  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary somewhat between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the laundered money into the legitimate economy\n\nCriminal penalties usually depend on factors like the amount of money involved and specific methods used.",
